          <p>The input grid has dimensions 7 x 7. It uses the following colors: White, Azure.
The output grid is expected to have dimensions 7 x 7. It is expected to use the following colors: White, Azure, Blue.
The input grid contains four objects - "blobs" of Azure.
The output grid is expected to contain four objects: "blobs" of Azure and a single pixel of Blue in each blob.

The transformation rule, based on previous training examples, is to replace the bottom-left most Azure pixel in each "blob" of Azure with a Blue pixel.

Let's implement this rule in code to generate a solution for the test input:


</p>
        

        

        

        
